headline: How Being Shortlisted for Sweden’s Ringhals Project Has Changed GE Vernova’s (GEV) Investment Story
summary: Vattenfall recently announced that GE Vernova and Rolls-Royce SMR have been shortlisted as the final candidates to supply modular nuclear reactors for a major new project at the Ringhals site on Sweden’s Varo Peninsula. This move positions GE Vernova as a key contender to deliver next-generation nuclear power in Europe, spotlighting its modular reactor technology and established supply chains. We'll explore how being named a finalist for the Ringhals project highlights GE Vernova’s position...
